{"current_version": "0.1", "project": "Module Template Project", "project_url": "https://eclipse-score.github.io/module_template/", "versions": {"0.1": {"creator": {"program": "sphinx_needs", "version": "8.0.0"}, "needs": {"comp__gatewayd": {"belongs_to": ["feat__someip_gateway"], "content": "Connects the :need:`comp__someipd` to the application via LoLa IPC (mw::com).", "docname": "architecture/components", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp__gatewayd", "lineno": 18, "safety": "ASIL_B", "section_name": "Components", "sections": ["Components"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "title": "SOME/IP Gateway Daemon", "type": "comp", "type_name": "Component"}, "comp__null_serializer": {"belongs_to": ["feat__someip_gateway"], "content": "A serializer that does not actually serialize or deserialize data, but only handles messages that are already serialized by the application.", "docname": "architecture/components", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp__null_serializer", "lineno": 51, "safety": "ASIL_B", "section_name": "Components", "sections": ["Components"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "title": "Null Serializer", "type": "comp", "type_name": "Component"}, "comp__serializer": {"belongs_to": ["feat__someip_gateway"], "content": "Serializer and deserializer for SOME/IP messages. Used by the :need:`comp__gatewayd`.\nThe serializer is built or configured especially for the application data types that it handles.", "docname": "architecture/components", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp__serializer", "lineno": 40, "safety": "ASIL_B", "section_name": "Components", "sections": ["Components"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "title": "SOME/IP Serializer", "type": "comp", "type_name": "Component"}, "comp__someipd": {"belongs_to": ["feat__someip_gateway"], "belongs_to_back": ["comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_offer_format", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_cyclic_timing", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_find_response", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_sub_lifecycle", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_phases_timing", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__msg_resp_header", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__msg_error_codes", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__evt_subscription"], "content": "Handles the SOME/IP communication with the network.", "docname": "architecture/components", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp__someipd", "lineno": 61, "safety": "QM", "section_name": "Components", "sections": ["Components"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "title": "SOME/IP Network Daemon", "type": "comp", "type_name": "Component"}, "comp_req__tc8_conformance__evt_subscription": {"belongs_to": ["comp__someipd"], "content": "The conformance test suite shall verify that ``someipd`` delivers\nNOTIFICATION messages (message type 0x02) with correct event ID\nonly to endpoints with an active eventgroup subscription, and ceases\ndelivery after StopSubscribeEventgroup.\n\nNote: Traces to SOME/IP specification section 5.1 (Events) and\nSOME/IP-SD section 4.1.2.4 (SubscribeEventgroup triggering\nnotification delivery). Covers TC8-EVT-001 through TC8-EVT-004\nand TC8-EVT-006 from the test strategy.", "docname": "tc8_conformance/requirements", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__tc8_conformance__evt_subscription", "lineno": 191, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies": ["feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance"], "section_name": "Component Requirements \u2014 Event Notification", "sections": ["Component Requirements \u2014 Event Notification", "TC8 Conformance Test Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "tags": ["tc8", "conformance", "events", "notification"], "title": "TC8 Event Notification Subscription Lifecycle", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__tc8_conformance__msg_error_codes": {"belongs_to": ["comp__someipd"], "content": "The conformance test suite shall verify that ``someipd`` returns\nthe correct SOME/IP return codes for error conditions:\n``E_UNKNOWN_SERVICE`` (0x02) for requests to non-existent services,\n``E_UNKNOWN_METHOD`` (0x03) for invalid method IDs, and\n``E_WRONG_INTERFACE_VERSION`` for interface version mismatches.\n\nNote: Traces to SOME/IP specification section 4.1.7 (Return Code)\nand the return code table (Table 4.14). Covers TC8-SOMEIP-MSG-003,\nTC8-SOMEIP-MSG-004, and TC8-SOMEIP-MSG-006 from the test strategy.", "docname": "tc8_conformance/requirements", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__tc8_conformance__msg_error_codes", "lineno": 168, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies": ["feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance"], "section_name": "Component Requirements \u2014 SOME/IP Message Format", "sections": ["Component Requirements \u2014 SOME/IP Message Format", "TC8 Conformance Test Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "tags": ["tc8", "conformance", "message_format", "error_handling"], "title": "TC8 SOME/IP Error Return Codes", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__tc8_conformance__msg_resp_header": {"belongs_to": ["comp__someipd"], "content": "The conformance test suite shall verify that ``someipd`` returns\nSOME/IP RESPONSE messages with correct protocol version (0x01),\nmessage type (0x80), matching session ID, and matching client ID\nfor each received REQUEST.\n\nNote: Traces to SOME/IP specification sections 4.1.4\n(Protocol Version), 4.1.6 (Message Type), and 4.1.3 (Request ID \u2014\nClient ID / Session ID). Covers TC8-SOMEIP-MSG-001,\nTC8-SOMEIP-MSG-002, TC8-SOMEIP-MSG-005, and TC8-SOMEIP-MSG-008\nfrom the test strategy.", "docname": "tc8_conformance/requirements", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__tc8_conformance__msg_resp_header", "lineno": 147, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies": ["feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance"], "section_name": "Component Requirements \u2014 SOME/IP Message Format", "sections": ["Component Requirements \u2014 SOME/IP Message Format", "TC8 Conformance Test Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "tags": ["tc8", "conformance", "message_format"], "title": "TC8 SOME/IP Response Header Validation", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_cyclic_timing": {"belongs_to": ["comp__someipd"], "content": "The conformance test suite shall verify that ``someipd`` repeats\nOfferService entries at the configured ``cyclic_offer_delay`` interval\n(\u00b120% tolerance) during the main phase of Service Discovery.\n\nNote: Traces to SOME/IP-SD specification section 4.1.1\n(SD Phases \u2014 Main Phase, cyclic offer behavior).\nCovers TC8-SD-003 from the test strategy.", "docname": "tc8_conformance/requirements", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_cyclic_timing", "lineno": 68, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies": ["feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance"], "section_name": "Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "sections": ["Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "TC8 Conformance Test Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "tags": ["tc8", "conformance", "service_discovery", "timing"], "title": "TC8 SD Cyclic Offer Timing", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_find_response": {"belongs_to": ["comp__someipd"], "content": "The conformance test suite shall verify that ``someipd`` responds to\na SOME/IP-SD FindService entry with a unicast OfferService for a\nknown service, and does not respond for an unknown service.\n\nNote: Traces to SOME/IP-SD specification section 4.1.2.2\n(FindService entry handling and response behavior).\nCovers TC8-SD-004 and TC8-SD-005 from the test strategy.", "docname": "tc8_conformance/requirements", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_find_response", "lineno": 86, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies": ["feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance"], "section_name": "Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "sections": ["Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "TC8 Conformance Test Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "tags": ["tc8", "conformance", "service_discovery"], "title": "TC8 SD FindService Response", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_offer_format": {"belongs_to": ["comp__someipd"], "content": "The conformance test suite shall verify that ``someipd`` transmits\nSOME/IP-SD OfferService entries on the configured multicast group\nwith correct service ID, instance ID, major/minor version, and TTL\nfields upon startup.\n\nNote: Traces to SOME/IP-SD specification sections 4.1.2.1\n(OfferService entry format) and 4.1.2.3 (Service Entry fields).\nCovers TC8-SD-001 and TC8-SD-002 from the test strategy.", "docname": "tc8_conformance/requirements", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_offer_format", "lineno": 49, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies": ["feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance"], "section_name": "Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "sections": ["Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "TC8 Conformance Test Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "tags": ["tc8", "conformance", "service_discovery"], "title": "TC8 SD Offer Entry Format Validation", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_phases_timing": {"belongs_to": ["comp__someipd"], "content": "The conformance test suite shall verify that ``someipd`` observes\nthe three SD phases: initial wait delay within ``[initial_delay_min,\ninitial_delay_max]``, repetition of offers ``repetitions_max`` times\nat ``repetitions_base_delay`` intervals, and transition to main phase.\n\nNote: Traces to SOME/IP-SD specification section 4.1.1\n(SD Phases \u2014 Initial Wait, Repetition, Main Phase).\nCovers TC8-SD-009 and TC8-SD-010 from the test strategy.", "docname": "tc8_conformance/requirements", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_phases_timing", "lineno": 125, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies": ["feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance"], "section_name": "Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "sections": ["Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "TC8 Conformance Test Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "tags": ["tc8", "conformance", "service_discovery", "timing"], "title": "TC8 SD Initial Delay and Repetitions Phase", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_sub_lifecycle": {"belongs_to": ["comp__someipd"], "content": "The conformance test suite shall verify that ``someipd`` correctly\nhandles the SubscribeEventgroup lifecycle: acknowledge valid\nsubscriptions (SubscribeEventgroupAck), reject unknown eventgroups\n(SubscribeEventgroupNack with TTL=0), and honor StopSubscribeEventgroup\nby ceasing notifications.\n\nNote: Traces to SOME/IP-SD specification sections 4.1.2.4\n(SubscribeEventgroup), 4.1.2.5 (StopSubscribeEventgroup),\nand 4.1.2.6 (SubscribeEventgroupAck/Nack).\nCovers TC8-SD-006, TC8-SD-007, and TC8-SD-008 from the test strategy.", "docname": "tc8_conformance/requirements", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_sub_lifecycle", "lineno": 104, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies": ["feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance"], "section_name": "Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "sections": ["Component Requirements \u2014 Service Discovery", "TC8 Conformance Test Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "tags": ["tc8", "conformance", "service_discovery", "eventgroup"], "title": "TC8 SD Subscribe Eventgroup Lifecycle", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "dec_rec__component__someip_gw_registration": {"context": "The SOME/IP Gateway architecture separates the core communication stack from multiple gateway processes. This is necessary for safety separation (ASIL vs. QM) and to manage a single network socket, which can only be bound by one process. A mechanism is required for the gateway \"client\" processes to inform the central \"server\" stack of their routing needs at runtime.", "decision": "Gateway processes will dynamically register their communication requirements (e.g., required services and events) with the central SOME/IP Communication Stack process. This will be achieved via a dedicated, message-based IPC interface.", "docname": "architecture/dec_someipgw_registration", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "dec_rec__component__someip_gw_registration", "lineno": 18, "section_name": "Architectural Design Decision: Dynamic Registration for SOME/IP Gateway", "sections": ["Architectural Design Decision: Dynamic Registration for SOME/IP Gateway"], "status": "proposed", "title": "Dynamic Registration for SOME/IP Gateway", "type": "dec_rec", "type_name": "Decision Record"}, "feat__someip_gateway": {"belongs_to_back": ["comp__gatewayd", "comp__serializer", "comp__null_serializer", "comp__someipd"], "content": "Dummy feature to comply to the meta-model.\nShould be defined in the process itself and only referenced.\nFor updating docs_as_code to version 4.x, this is required.", "docname": "architecture/features", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "feat__someip_gateway", "lineno": 19, "safety": "QM", "section_name": "Features", "sections": ["Features"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "title": "SOME/IP gateway", "type": "feat", "type_name": "Feature"}, "feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance": {"content": "The SOME/IP Gateway project shall verify protocol conformance of its\nSOME/IP stack (``someipd``) against OPEN Alliance TC8 SOME/IP test\nspecifications at the wire protocol level, without requiring application\nprocesses.\n\nNote: The ``:satisfies:`` link targets a placeholder stakeholder requirement.\nThis shall be updated to reference the upstream S-CORE stakeholder requirement\nfor SOME/IP interoperability once it is formally defined.", "docname": "tc8_conformance/requirements", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance", "lineno": 24, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies": ["stkh_req__docgen_enabled__example"], "satisfies_back": ["comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_offer_format", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_cyclic_timing", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_find_response", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_sub_lifecycle", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__sd_phases_timing", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__msg_resp_header", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__msg_error_codes", "comp_req__tc8_conformance__evt_subscription"], "section_name": "Feature Requirement", "sections": ["Feature Requirement", "TC8 Conformance Test Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "valid", "tags": ["tc8", "conformance", "someip", "verification"], "title": "TC8 SOME/IP Protocol Conformance", "type": "feat_req", "type_name": "Feature Requirement"}, "stkh_req__docgen_enabled__example": {"docname": "requirements/stakeholder", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "stkh_req__docgen_enabled__example", "lineno": 23, "rationale": "Ensure documentation builds are possible for all modules", "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "QM", "satisfies_back": ["feat_req__tc8_conformance__conformance"], "section_name": "Stakeholder Requirements", "sections": ["Stakeholder Requirements"], "security": "YES", "status": "valid", "title": "Example Functional Requirement", "type": "stkh_req", "type_name": "Stakeholder Requirement"}}, "needs_amount": 16, "needs_defaults_removed": true, "needs_schema": {"$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#", "properties": {"approved_by": {"default": [], "description": "Link field", "field_type": "links", "items": {"type": "string"}, "type": "array"}, "approved_by_back": {"default": [], "description": "Backlink field", "field_type": "backlinks", "items": {"type": "string"